{
  "texts": [
    "It examined how different communication tones between agents and clinicians-suggestive (non-assertive) versus imposing (assertive)-affect clinician receptivity and performance.",
    "Findings suggested that assertive agents can reduce medical errors and increase satisfaction, offering a new approach to adaptive communication in healthcare.",
    "This work has advanced human-computer interaction by emphasizing the importance of clinician-centred, intelligent agent design and offers valuable insights for future healthcare innovations.",
    "[5] Another study developed a deep learning (DL) model to improve skin cancer classification, addressing class imbalance and enhancing interpretability.",
    "Using the HAM10000 dataset, an optimized CNN identified seven cancer types with 82% accuracy and 0.47% loss."
  ]
}